Mr. Ditta betrayed this confidence and tried to hide behind the varnish of his profession.
The Lancashire Serious and Organized Crime Unit conducted the investigation into Mr. Ditta, who was convicted of the three counts of possession of cocaine and now obstruction of justice, testifying to his commitment to prosecute criminals.
