They want the government to give priority to new trade links with countries such as China, India and Brazil rather than getting bogged down in the long and arduous process of reforming European institutional arcanes.
When asked about specific policy issues – ranging from monopoly regulation to product laws – the majority of entrepreneurs believe that control of these key competencies should return to Westminster.
