Finally, and more importantly, our survey of business leaders revealed that a large majority wanted Britain to pursue initiatives to change the Treaty and develop a trade-based relationship with the EU, not politics.
This conclusion, which can be found in all major groups and companies of all sizes, shows that the business world insists on a "significant change" that restores power to the UK.
The stakes are high – achieving a change in the treaty and better representing Britain's interests would make it possible to see a 16% shift in votes in favour of maintaining the country in the EU in a referendum.
