But Mr Hare rejected the idea that the YMCA had a cultural problem preventing staff from reporting Lord's failures to protect children.
The staff members testified that they had observed certain shortcomings, including the fact that Lord remained alone with the children, that he kept them in private, that they sat on his lap, that he loved them, and that he let them play with his mobile phone.
Danielle Ockwell, who was under Lord's guidance and had requested training in child protection because she was concerned about her behaviour, said she found YMCA Caringbah's child services manager, Jacqui Barnat, who framed Lord "very intimidating and difficult to approach most of the time."
